problem.markdown:
We are in 2006 and we are interested in testing a new activation function: the softplus function:

\(\text{Softplus(x)}=\beta∗\ln(1+\exp(\beta∗x))\) where \(\beta\) is a hyperparameter.

<img src="/static/Module_3_Question_5_softplus_figure_1.png" height="300" alt="A graph of the softplus activation function. At x=0, the output is the natural logarithm of 2 (ln 2). Going to the left (x headed toward minus infinity, the output converges toward 0. Going to the right (x headed toward infinity), the output converges to a linear function with a slope equal to beta."/>

We need to implement the forward, backward and update methods of a new softplus module. To simplify, we are setting β=2. Provide your answer with 3 significant figures (e.g. 1.23e-1) or round to 0 if smaller than 1e-2.

>> a) To test your forward implementation, determine the expected outputs of the forward pass associated with the following inputs with three significant digits: [-6, 0, 6]. <<

( )  [0.00, 2.00, 4.00] {{Incorrect}}
( )  [0.00, 1.00, 6.00] {{Incorrect}}
(x)  [0.00, 1.39, 24.0] {{Correct}}
( )  [-1.00, 1.00, 1.00] {{Incorrect}}

>> b) To test your backward implementation, determine the expected outputs of the backward pass associated with the following inputs to the forward pass: [-6, 0, 6]. So, you must calculate the forward pass first (question a)), and then the backward pass.<<

( )  [0.00, 1.39, 24.0] {{Incorrect}}
(x)  [0.00, 2.00, 4.00] {{Correct}}
( )  [0.00, 2.00, 3.00] {{Incorrect}}
( )  [0.00, 1.00, 5.00] {{Incorrect}}

>> c) Which activation function is similar to the softplus activation function? <<

( ) Sigmoid {{Incorrect}}
(x) ReLU {{Correct}}
( ) Tanh {{Incorrect}}
( ) Linear {{Incorrect}}
